      "writtenOn": "2020-07-20T13:34:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "These are different ideas. Bicubic is conceptually treating the image pixels as point samples of a smooth function and interpolating values between those samples using a piecewise cubic function (in both dimensions). It\u0027s analogous to computing intermediate points in our patch primitive.",
      "parentUuid": "a00ab757_cf6656a3",
      "revId": "1b1c1d8cb4a0ffa883181af6ca3bc4622859120f",
